Alternate set identification number. If SID=0, the set identification number is obtained from the METHOD command in CASECC and used to select the EIGR, EIGB, or EIGRL entries in DYNAMIC. Similarly for CMETHOD and EIGC. If SID>0, then METHOD command is ignored and the EIGR, EIGB, or EIGRL is selected by this parameter value. All subsequent parameter values (METH, F1, etc.) are ignored. Similarly for CMETHOD and EIGC for Lanczos method only. If SID<0, then both the METHOD command and all EIGR, EIGB, or EIGRL entries are ignored and the subsequent parameter values (METH, F1, etc.) will be used to control the eigenvalue extraction.
